N:ralph
D:Ouroboros specification-first development + persistent completion. Use when the user needs a Socratic interview before coding, an immutable seed/spec, drift-aware execution, or a keep-going-until-verified loop. `ralph` is the portable method anchor; route Claude/Codex/Gemini runtime details to omc/omx/ohmg and approval posture to ralphmode.
G:ralph ouroboros specification-first socratic interview seed spec immutable requirements ambiguity reduction drift evaluate evolve persistent completion keep going until verified ooo
U[6]:
1:Vague requirements that need clarification before code is written
2:Requests to freeze an immutable seed/spec before implementation
3:Tasks that must keep going until tests/checks/acceptance criteria pass
4:Drift-aware implementation against an original contract
5:Repeated failures requiring deliberate unstuck routing
6:Portable method questions rather than platform-specific runtime setup
S[8]{n,action,details}:
1:interview,Socratic clarification,ooo interview "topic" → reduce ambiguity to ≤0.2 before seeding
2:seed,Freeze immutable spec,ooo seed → lock goal/constraints/acceptance criteria/ontology
3:run,Execute against seed,ooo run [seed.yaml] → Discover→Define→Design→Deliver
4:evaluate,Verify before done,ooo evaluate <id> → Mechanical→Semantic→Consensus gate; drift 0.00-0.15 excellent / 0.15-0.30 watch / 0.30+ correct
5:evolve,Stabilize changing ontology,ooo evolve "topic" [--no-execute] → continue until convergence is strong enough
6:ralph,Persistent completion loop,ooo ralph "task" → execute→verify→adjust→continue until verified or capped; completion promises help but verified completion is the real stop rule
7:unstuck,Choose a recovery mindset,ooo unstuck [simplifier|hacker|contrarian|researcher|architect] → match persona to failure pattern
8:route-out,Keep boundaries clean,platform runtime setup → omc/omx/ohmg; approvals/trust → ralphmode; integrated ledger/review → jeo
R[6]:
1:Do not code while ambiguity is still high
2:Once generated, the seed is the baseline for drift checks
3:Verified completion matters more than emitting a promise token
4:`ralph` is the method anchor, not a catch-all runtime wrapper
5:Use the live local path `.agent-skills/ralph/...` in setup examples
6:If runtime docs drift, fix references or sibling runtime skills instead of bloating this front door
E[4]{desc,in,out}:
1:{Clarify a vague build request,ooo interview "build a task management CLI",Questions reduce ambiguity and identify goal/constraints/success before any implementation starts}
2:{Freeze a seed before coding,ooo seed,A locked spec with goal/constraints/acceptance criteria/ontology is created and treated as immutable}
3:{Persistent verified loop,ooo ralph "fix all failing tests" --max-iterations=10,Work repeats with verification checkpoints until checks pass or the loop cap is reached}
4:{Runtime boundary question,How do I wire Codex-native hooks for ralph?,Routes concrete Codex runtime setup to omx or platform references while keeping ralph positioned as the portable method}
